# Email and Twitter Notifications Setup

The Python script [check_snow_status.py](file:///Users/I808883/.gemini/antigravity/brain/e32ba253-8e99-4635-9848-02b00fb21049/check_snow_status.py) now supports Email and Twitter notifications when snow cleaning is complete.

## Email Notifications (Gmail)

1. **Enable 2-Factor Authentication** on your Gmail account
2. **Generate an App Password**:
   - Go to [Google Account Settings](https://myaccount.google.com/)
   - Security → 2-Step Verification → App passwords
   - Select "Mail" and your device
   - Copy the generated 16-character password

3. **Create `.env` file** (copy from [.env.example](file:///Users/I808883/.gemini/antigravity/brain/e32ba253-8e99-4635-9848-02b00fb21049/.env.example)):
   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env
   ```

4. **Edit `.env`** and set:
   ```
   EMAIL_ENABLED=true
   EMAIL_FROM=your-email@gmail.com
   EMAIL_TO=recipient@example.com
   EMAIL_PASSWORD=your-16-char-app-password
   SMTP_SERVER=smtp.gmail.com
   SMTP_PORT=587
   ```

## Twitter Notifications

1. **Get Twitter API Access**:
   - Go to [Twitter Developer Portal](https://developer.twitter.com/en/portal/dashboard)
   - Create a new Project and App
   - Under "User authentication settings", enable OAuth 1.0a with Read and Write permissions
   - Generate API Key, API Secret, Access Token, and Access Token Secret

2. **Install tweepy**:
   ```bash
   pip install tweepy
   ```

3. **Edit `.env`** and set:
   ```
   TWITTER_ENABLED=true
   TWITTER_API_KEY=your-api-key
   TWITTER_API_SECRET=your-api-secret
   TWITTER_ACCESS_TOKEN=your-access-token
   TWITTER_ACCESS_SECRET=your-access-secret
   ```

## Usage

Run the script with polling enabled:
```bash
python3 check_snow_status.py --section 14 --poll 60
```

When the section is completed, the script will:
- ✅ Show a desktop notification
- ✅ Send an email (if configured)
- ✅ Post a tweet (if configured)

## Security Note

**Never commit your `.env` file to Git!** It contains sensitive credentials. The `.env` file is already in `.gitignore`.
